The paper deals with deep learning-based image segmentation, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel method to predict segmentation quality without ground truth, which involves training two neural networks (REC-Net and REG-Net) for image reconstruction and quality score regression, respectively. This approach involves regression and optimization techniques, which are also common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the ACDC17 dataset, which is related to medical imaging (cs.MM). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of robustness against adversarial attacks, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
